Quote:  The clematis, campanula trachelium, or bell flower, whose hues, white, red, and yellow, with the convolvulus, or bind-weed, and immumerable liands, [106] hung around in pleasing disorder. <i>Ibid.</i> 2/134 The Campanula or bell flower of various hues, pink, yellow, and white was observable, climbing around the stalk of every shrub of sufficient strength to bear its light weight.
